            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Somerville International School is good school in Delhi NCR region. Their focus is on academics yet they spend right amount of time and effort on extra curricular activities like Music, Art & Craft, Football, Basketball, Aerobics etc. Teachers are well groomed and handles students well.\n\nThe school building is nice and lots of plantations are there. Focused approach towards keeping the environment green and clean.\n\n\"Despite these good things School management is very weak in communication. Most of the time either they do not send any communication or their communication is contradictory. To their convenience sometimes they use MS team for the last minute change in communication and sometimes they use email. There is absolutely no audit trail of any such communication. Despite giving continued feedback, School is doing the same thing again and again. The top management of the School must intervene to assess the situation and further improve.\"\n\n|| Update from recent past experience ||\n\nA significant improvement is now seen in the communication for the last couple of months ever since they have started using WhatsApp mode of communication. School Management has also provided dedicated mobile numbers to get in touch with the School and teacher.\n\nHowever, School Management should focus on retaining good teachers. There is a high rate of mobilization in the teachers feternity in the school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
